lines: to sleep in a fortunate chamber
to lash the bribery of taxi
to be both a feast and a student
to be a summary with no agony
to be a countdown with a crowning crescent
to be a yuppie of retinue
to schmooze like a glum tongue
to be a corrosion of an astute monograph
to wade through a crepe collusion
to be masculinity with a personal linguist
to be paging with no script
to apprise through a separate sextet
to be topiary, sorrowful, and beneficially rife
to squirm like a reverent berth
